    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-07-03T18:05:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-07-03T18:05:00-05:00" n="660"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d660">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/7–353: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Korea</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d660fn1">This telegram, drafted and cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName>, was repeated to Tokyo for
                            <persName corresp="#p_CGMW1">Clark</persName> as 39.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-07-03T19:05:00-04:00"
                            >July 3, 1953—7:05 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. If <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName>’s reply to your July 3 <hi
                        rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> and letter<note n="2" xml:id="d660fn2"
                        >Transmitted in Army message 0217502, July 3, <ref target="#pg_1312">p.
                            1312</ref>.</note> is still unsatisfactory the time has probably come
                    for you to leave if you feel that your continued presence will serve no useful
                    purpose.</p>
                <p>Would appreciate your judgment and recommendations as to line of action be taken
                    at time of your departure in connection with following: <list>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                        <item>Coordination your departure and action taken connection therewith with
                            actions being taken by <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>
                            accordance his CX 63449<note n="3" xml:id="d660fn3">Dated July 2, <ref
                                    target="#pg_1296">p. 1296</ref>.</note> so as to produce maximum
                            impact upon <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> and <gloss
                                target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> political and military leaders.</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                        <item>How and to what extent you should make clear to <persName
                                corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> that in event of his continued
                            refusal to agree to the conditions upon which they were predicated, the
                            offers which have been made to him to obtain his cooperation are to be
                            considered as withdrawn when you depart.</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                        <item>How and to what extent you should make clear to <persName
                                corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> that his present course action
                            makes it necessary for <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> plan for the
                            “another arrangement” indicated in President’s June 18 letter<note n="4"
                                xml:id="d660fn4">Not printed, but see footnote 3 to telegram 13 from
                                Seoul, <ref target="#pg_1221">p. 1221</ref>.</note> and that <gloss
                                target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss> has been authorized take
                            necessary steps this regard.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>With regard public relations aspects at time your departure would appreciate your
                    views concerning issuance of public statement by you and to what extent it
                    should cover following points: <list>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                        <item>Detail extreme lengths to which US has been prepared go to meet
                                <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> viewpoint while <persName
                                corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> remaining intransigent and refusing
                            give assurances cooperation in conclusion and implementation
                            armistice.</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                        <item>While <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> made concession on
                            minor points he has insisted US commit itself resume hostilities for
                            purpose achieving unification if political conference following
                            armistice fails achieve unification within ninety days. <persName
                                corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName>’s proposal means armistice not firm
                            and binding conclusion hostilities which <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                                >UNC</gloss> has consistently demanded of Communists but only
                            temporary ceasefire which can be broken at will by either side.
                            Conclusion armistice would mean successful achievement UN military
                            objectives in Korea by repelling aggression. If <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                                >ROK</gloss> cooperation forthcoming US resolves to work with <gloss
                                target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> by all peaceful means to effect
                            unification. However US not prepared commit itself resort to war to
                            achieve this purpose. It is up to <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> to
                            decide whether it wishes receive cooperation US this great
                            endeavor.</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                        <item>Generous and far-reaching offers of US having been rejected by
                                <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> these offers now
                            withdrawn.</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> will continue seek armistice with
                            Communists on basis <persName corresp="#p_CGMW1">Clark</persName>’s
                            letter June 29.<note n="5" xml:id="d660fn5">For text, see Department of
                                State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, July 13, 1953, pp.
                                46–47.</note>
                        </item>
                        <pb facs="0207" n="1325" xml:id="pg_1325"/>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">e</hi>.</label>
                        <item>Release Secretary’s letter June 22<note n="6" xml:id="d660fn6">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1238">p.
                                1238</ref>.</note> to <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> and
                            such of your communications you consider useful.</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">f</hi>.</label>
                        <item>Foregoing possibly to be supplemented by background press conference
                            in as much detail you consider desirable.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>In addition views on foregoing would appreciate any other views and
                    recommendations you may have so that appropriate recommendations may be
                    submitted to President and any action required here can be coordinated with that
                    to be taken by you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
